The paper deals with black-box complexity theory and evolutionary algorithms, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational intelligence (cs.NE). However, the paper also introduces a new model that combines features of ranking-based and memory-restricted black-box models, which are relevant to the subfields of data structures (cs.DS) and data mining (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the performance of algorithms, which is relevant to the subfield of computational complexity (cs.CC) and machine learning (cs.LG).
